# Config Persistence Safety

- Treat `~/.klaw/config.toml` as shared mutable state across GUI panels, helpers, and runtime-facing editors.
- Never mutate a cached `AppConfig` snapshot and then write the whole file back later. That pattern causes last-writer-wins data loss.
- For partial config edits, always follow `reload latest on-disk config -> mutate the target subsection -> validate -> persist`.
- Prefer centralized `ConfigStore` update helpers over panel-local `toml::to_string_pretty(...) + save_raw_toml(...)` flows.
- When changing config persistence logic, add a regression test that proves two stale editors saving different fields do not clobber each other.

# Example

```rust
// Good: update from the latest on-disk config before saving.
store.update_config(|config| {
    config.memory.embedding.model = "text-embedding-v4".to_string();
    Ok(())
})?;
```
